1.title: New Zip Part Two
1.plot: The build is underway on the ultimate custom car shop -the new West Coast Customs. Ryan's dream of an automotive theme park is almost a reality, but there is still a long way to go before it's ready to build cars. History is about to be made!

2.title: Top Up Top Down
2.plot: With the new shop open it's time to start building. Ryan has a new client who wants to build a 68 convertible Mustang for his wife's 50th birthday. It matches up perfectly with the 67 Mustang Fastback that needs to be built from the old shop.

3.title: Jack N' 4 Beats
3.plot: Jack Daniel's is in search of the hottest unsigned artist is hip-hop, and they need West Coast Customs help to turn their old, beat up trailer into a professional mobile studio that they can take on the road and find the next hip-hop star

4.title: BBQ's Galore
4.plot: BBQ's Galore has challenged the team at West Coast Customs to create a mobile showroom that they can take to events and set up quickly. Now the team has to open up a box truck, make it practical and of course, make it cool.

5.title: Sema
5.plot: After missing last year, The West Coast Customs Experience is back at the SEMA convention and ready to dominate. WCC and Toyota host the experience - a place where students will work with the WCC team to build 4 Toyotas all in the span of one week.

6.title: Slingshaq
6.plot: Shaq wants a Polaris Slingshot, the only problem is he's too big to fit. Now the team at West Coast Customs must figure out how to stretch and shape this vehicle in order to house his 7' 1" frame and size 22 feet.

7.title: Larry's Tailgate 2000
7.plot: Dr. Pepper wants to do something special for there iconic salesman Larry Culpepper. WCC decides to transform a RV to his dream super car.

1.title: AquaFlash
1.plot: The comic book world descends on WCC when Kia and DC Entertainment tap Ryan and the crew to build two super hero inspired cars. Watch as WCC transform a Forte Koup and a Rio into two of the Justice League's superheros - the Flash and Aquaman.

2.title: Line-X -WCC Body Armour
2.plot: WCC sets out to prove that Line-X isn't for bedliners anymore. The team will create a special 2013 Camaro that will be Line-X'd inside and out. And since they are the premier custom car shop on the planet, they won't stop there.

3.title: South of the Border Buses
3.plot: It's time to head south of the Boarder for this build. The Ohana Group has challenged WCC to create the ultimate Taco and Margarita buses that they can use for clients at the new Maravilla resort in Cabo San Lucas.

4.title: Attack of the Monster Kids
4.plot: From homeless to hip-hop stars, Chi Towns finest have seen it all. But when Monster Cable pulls Ryan in to help build them a new van to travel in, they're really given something to dance about. WCC will take a Sprinter Van and transform it into the Ultimate tour bus.

5.title: Technoliner
5.plot: It's time to take buses to the next level. Which is exactly what WCC does for CDW- the leading provider of technology solutions. West Coast Customs will create the Technoliner- Old school styling meets tech. It's WCC's biggest build yet.

6.title: Chris Brown's First Love Lamborghini
6.plot: You only have one first love, and for Chris Brown it's his 2004 Lamborgini. But this r&b sensation can't be seen driving last years whip, so he's asked Ryan to update his baby into something new. And the crew at WCC are up to the challenge.

7.title: Smurfs Come to WCC
7.plot: Watch as Ryan and co. take a trip to Smurf village to build four of the smurfiest vehicles around. Just in time for the Smurfs 2 movie, the crew at WCC will take Dash cars and transform them using hard work and creativity, into Smurfmobiles.

8.title: Cool-Capable Braun Explorer
8.plot: West Coast Customs teams up with Indy race legend Sam Schmidt to move beyond the soccer mom mini-van and bring the cool factor into a one of a kind handicap accessible vehicle.

9.title: eBay Motors: The Road Home
9.plot: In honor of Veteran's Day, the team at WCC join forces with eBay to create cars for 3 deserving vets. WCC will transform a van into a paint ball troop transport, a Suburban into a hot rod family car, and give a Wildcats fan the Mustang of her dreams.

10.title: Cracker Jack'd
10.plot: In order to promote Cracker Jack'd, the "snack with an impact", the WCC team do the impossible once again. This time by transforming an RV into something truly impactful, a Mobile Dunk Tank. But will it hold water? Or will WCC sink under pressure.

1.title: Kid's Kaddy
1.plot: Detroit born superstar Kid Rock loves his 1970's Cadillac, but wants to bring some of the bling back. Ryan and the WCC team have their work cut out for them - to bring this Detroit classic into the 21st century, while keeping that 70's vibe.

2.title: Mad Max
2.plot: The video game car has come to life in WCC. Warner Brothers taps the skills of West Coast Customs to combine a 1970's Maverick and a 1990's Ranger into an exact replica of the Mad Max Magnum Opus car. Next stop, the Wasteland.

3.title: Who's the Boss
3.plot: Getting your first car is a big deal, especially when your dad is the King of Customs. "Little" Ryan Friedlinghaus takes the reins on this build to work with the guys on the ultimate first whip. WCC-style.

4.title: The West Coast Customs Experience
4.plot: The shop is moving to Vegas...for the week of SEMA. The Experience is back as the WCC team set up shop at the SEMA convention and work side by side with their fans to build some beautiful cars.

5.title: Looking Back
5.plot: It's greatest hits time as Ryan reminisces about some of the crazy builds that West Coast Customs has done over the last couple of years. From AquaFlash to Zippo Jeep, check out what the West Coast Customs team has been up to.

6.title: Continental Tire Corvette
6.plot: It's game on for Continental Tires and WCC. Continental Tires wants to create something special for the U.S.A. vs. Mexico Soccer game, and WCC is the team to deliver. The crew will partner with Line-X to create Big Rig, and a new Stingray in Continental yellow just in time for the game.

7.title: El Rusty
7.plot: Hall of Fame Racer Rusty Wallace knows his cars. And when he saw this beauty of an El Camino he knew he had to have it. But Rusty can't be driving a stock car, so he calls on the WCC team to create a daily driver fit for a racing legend.

8.title: Esurance Fantasy Build
8.plot: Esurance and West Coast Customs have partnered up to build the car of tomorrow. So they've reached out to fans for their ideas. Now it's up to the team at WCC to bring those dreams to life.

9.title: Nest Protects
9.plot: Where there's smoke, there's fire. Watch as Ryan and the boys West Coast Customize a FireTruck to highlight the power of the company Nest.

10.title: BatSUV
10.plot: When West Coast Customs built the "batmobile", a matte black Cadillac CTS-V for pop star Justin Bieber, his dad loved it so much that he needed one to. Now it's up to the team at WCC to build a family-friendly "batmobile". The BatSUV.

11.title: Raise the Roof
11.plot: The 2015 Toyota Sienna is about to be released and Toyota is looking to make a statement. So they call on the team at West Coast Customs to "raise the roof" on their Swagger Wagon and create a DJ Van to end all DJ Vans.

12.title: WCC's New Zip Part 1
12.plot: It's WCC's biggest build yet, only this time it's not a car, it's a building. WCC is moving to a new zip code. Corona was great, but Burbank is even better. Ryan has big plans to make WCC the best custom car shop on the planet.

imdb.title: West Coast Customs
plot: Chronicling the a car-customizing shop in Corona, Cal., and their clients' project vehicles.::sprywolf
